In a #small pot{}, combine @Chicken Stock Concentrate{2}, @Honey{2%tsp}, half the @White Wine Vinegar{5%tsp} (you'll use the rest later), half the @Sage{1/4%oz}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, @Cinnamon{1/4%tsp} (be sure to measure; we sent more), @Salt{1%tsp}, and a pinch of @Pepper{}.

> For 4 servings, use all the sage, 2 cups water, ½ tsp cinnamon, and 1¾ tsp salt.

Add @Butter{4%tbsp} and warm over medium heat until butter has melted.

While braising liquid heats, wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and halve @Parsnip{6%oz} lengthwise; cut on a diagonal into ¾-inch-thick pieces. Trim, peel and cut @Carrot{6%oz} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces (halve any thicker carrots lengthwise; the parsnip and carrot pieces should be roughly the same size). Position the flat side of your #knife{} over @Garlic{1%clove}. Using the heel of your hand, carefully hit the flat of the blade 1-2 times to smash garlic; remove peel and discard.

Once butter has melted in #pot{} with braising liquid, add parsnips, carrots, and garlic; partially cover pot with #lid{}. Continue to cook over medium heat for ~{10%minutes}.

Reduce heat to medium low. Cook until veggies are tender and easily pierced with a fork, ~{15-20%minutes} more.

While veggies braise, in a #large bowl{}, combine half the @Dijon Mustard{2%tsp}, remaining vinegar, @Olive Oil{2 1/2%tbsp}, @Sugar{1/4%tsp}, salt, and pepper. Whisk to combine.

> For 4 servings, use all @Dijon Mustard{4%tsp}, @Olive Oil{5%tbsp}, and @Sugar{1/2%tsp}.

Stir in @Dried Cranberries{1%oz}. Set aside, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

Pat @Beef Tenderloin Filets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with half the @Bold & Savory Steak Spice{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper.

> For 4 servings, use all the @Bold & Savory Steak Spice{2%tbsp}.

Once veggies have braised 15 minutes, heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest at least ~{5%minutes}. Slice beef against the grain. Wash out pan.

Return same pan to stovetop over medium-high heat. Add 1/3 cup braising liquid (2/3 cup for 4 servings) from pot and bring to a simmer. Cook until reduced and thickened, ~{1-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat; stir in @Butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

To bowl with dressing, add @Mixed Greens{2%oz}, @Croutons{1}, and half the @Parmesan Cheese{3%tbsp}; toss to coat. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Using a #slotted spoon{}, remove braised veggies from pot; divide between plates. Arrange steak and salad on the side. Spoon sauce over steak; sprinkle salad with remaining Parmesan. Serve.